WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:08.095
[ Life on Eris' "Silent Night"
plays ]

00:08.138 --> 00:12.273
♪♪

00:12.316 --> 00:16.625
♪ Silent night

00:16.668 --> 00:20.411
♪ Holy night

00:20.455 --> 00:23.980
♪ All is calm

00:24.024 --> 00:28.071
♪ All is bright

00:28.115 --> 00:30.595
♪ Round yon virgin

00:30.639 --> 00:31.901
Oh, um --
I'm sorry.
Hey.

00:31.944 --> 00:33.729
Hey, man.
Oh, sorry.Gibson.

00:33.772 --> 00:34.817
Sorry.

00:34.860 --> 00:35.948
He's three sheets
to the wind.

00:35.992 --> 00:38.212
You're drunk,
Gibson?

00:38.255 --> 00:40.779
I was not supposed to be
out today, so...

00:40.823 --> 00:42.172
Eh, I dragged him out.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.566
I thought
he needed some air

00:44.609 --> 00:46.350
and the smell
of pine trees.

00:46.394 --> 00:48.091
Yeah, yeah. Same. I mean, I --
You know, look, we usually

00:48.135 --> 00:49.658
do our tree shopping
as a family,

00:49.701 --> 00:53.053
but the boys have homework,
and I just really needed a walk.

00:53.096 --> 00:56.969
Um, I'm gonna go check out
those Balsam Firs.

00:57.013 --> 00:58.623
Was that Pru?
No.

00:58.667 --> 00:59.842
No, but she really
looks like her, though,

00:59.885 --> 01:01.278
doesn't she?Marsha: Wow, that's pretty.

01:01.322 --> 01:03.193
The Millers,
are they --

01:03.237 --> 01:05.195
Oh, they are officially
contesting the will, yeah.

01:05.239 --> 01:06.544
They've let us see Pru,

01:06.588 --> 01:08.720
like, maybe twice
in the last three weeks.

01:09.678 --> 01:10.983
I hate everything now.

01:12.115 --> 01:13.377
I didn't think
it was possible

01:13.421 --> 01:14.726
to hate Christmas trees,

01:14.770 --> 01:17.599
but I hate those now, too.

01:17.642 --> 01:19.079
Do I need to worry
about you, Gibson?

01:19.122 --> 01:20.732
[ Chuckles ]
You gonna stop drinking

01:20.776 --> 01:22.038
in time
for shift tomorrow?

01:22.082 --> 01:24.171
No -- Eh, you don't,
and I am,

01:24.214 --> 01:28.088
because Marsha
confiscated my whiskey.

01:28.131 --> 01:30.916
♪♪

01:30.960 --> 01:32.918
♪ Christ the savior is born...

01:32.962 --> 01:34.311
Maya: [ Chuckles ]
I always --

01:34.355 --> 01:35.791
Carina: You never
used them as a kid?
Yeah.

01:35.834 --> 01:36.835
Open pipes?
Yeah.

01:36.879 --> 01:38.185
Are they safe?
Mm-hmm.

01:38.228 --> 01:39.664
[ Oven timer dings ]Oh, cookies.

01:39.708 --> 01:41.753
I always wanted
a GI Joe set.

01:41.797 --> 01:43.407
Keep it.
Keep it?

01:43.451 --> 01:45.583
It's for
Toys for Tots.

01:45.627 --> 01:47.629
I'm not stealing toys
from needy children.

01:47.672 --> 01:49.761
Come on.Something smells good.

01:49.805 --> 01:51.111
That's Carina's baking.

01:51.154 --> 01:52.199
Nonna's recipe.

01:52.242 --> 01:53.374
She just told me

01:53.417 --> 01:56.377
to steal toys
from Toys for Tots.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.988
I'm getting you
a toy army guy for Christmas.

01:59.945 --> 02:01.295
You know,
you can't leave

02:01.338 --> 02:03.035
your divorce papers
in the freezer forever.

02:03.079 --> 02:05.560
♪ From now on, our troubles...♪

02:05.603 --> 02:07.431
There's no rule
that says that.

02:07.475 --> 02:09.520
♪ ...of sight♪

02:09.564 --> 02:10.521
[ Sighs ]

02:10.565 --> 02:11.653
Try.

02:12.871 --> 02:14.482
What am I
supposed to do?

02:14.525 --> 02:15.178
I don't know.

02:15.222 --> 02:16.962
Mmm.

02:17.006 --> 02:18.964
That is so good.

02:19.008 --> 02:20.575
Yeah.
We'll give her a cookie.

02:20.618 --> 02:21.489
Mmm.Yeah.

02:21.532 --> 02:23.491
♪♪

02:23.534 --> 02:25.362
[ Both chuckle ]

02:25.406 --> 02:27.451
Mnh-mnh. Mm. Nope.

02:27.495 --> 02:29.018
I can't wait anymore.
I have to give it to you now.

02:29.061 --> 02:30.889
Um, I think
we were getting there.

02:30.933 --> 02:32.804
No. [ Chuckles ]
Your Christmas present.

02:32.848 --> 02:34.371
You'll get the other thing
after. Don't worry.

02:34.415 --> 02:36.547
Oh.
Oh, that reminds me.

02:36.591 --> 02:38.027
Uh, I invited my mom

02:38.070 --> 02:39.594
to stay with us
for Christmas.

02:39.637 --> 02:41.204
[ Chuckles ]
Ignoring that.

02:41.248 --> 02:42.988
♪ Here we are as in olden days♪

02:43.032 --> 02:43.989
[ Sighs ]

02:45.513 --> 02:46.862
What --
Okay.

02:46.905 --> 02:49.647
Where did you even
hide that?
In Vic's room.

02:49.691 --> 02:50.648
Alright.
[ Chuckles ]

02:50.692 --> 02:51.562
You ready?Yeah.

02:51.606 --> 02:52.694
Okay, cool.

02:52.737 --> 02:53.695
♪♪

02:53.738 --> 02:56.132
Merry Christmas.

02:56.176 --> 02:57.655
[ Chuckles ]

02:57.699 --> 02:59.222
It -- It might need

02:59.266 --> 03:01.181
some highlights
around the eyes still,

03:01.224 --> 03:03.313
a little bit, but...

03:03.357 --> 03:04.706
Do you hate it?

03:04.749 --> 03:06.055
No.
No?

03:06.098 --> 03:07.796
I-I love it.

03:07.839 --> 03:09.624
Yeah?Yeah.

03:09.667 --> 03:12.453
I can't believe it.Yeah.

03:12.496 --> 03:13.671
You painted me.

03:13.715 --> 03:15.020
Yeah.

03:15.064 --> 03:16.196
Yeah, I mean,
it's not too cheesy?

03:16.239 --> 03:18.241
I just --
I thought you looked so --

03:18.285 --> 03:20.287
Uh-huh. Okay, thank you,
thank you, Dr. Altman.

03:20.330 --> 03:21.766
I'm good to go!
Oh! Yeah?

03:21.810 --> 03:23.246
They cleared you?

03:23.290 --> 03:24.508
Yeah,
I'm coming back to work.Yes!

03:24.552 --> 03:25.901
Oh, wow.
That seems kinda soon.

03:25.944 --> 03:27.816
Oh, she said another week
if I wasn't feeling good,

03:27.859 --> 03:31.776
but I am, so I'm cleared,
and sweet baby Jesus.

03:31.820 --> 03:34.301
Look at
this painting.

03:34.344 --> 03:38.392
♪ ...a merry little Christmas

03:38.435 --> 03:42.613
♪ Now

03:42.657 --> 03:44.267
Travis: I'm telling you,
it was like

03:44.311 --> 03:47.096
the most romantic gesture
anyone's ever done.

03:47.139 --> 03:49.229
And you hate it.I don't hate it.
It's just --

03:49.272 --> 03:50.534
It's too much.

03:50.578 --> 03:51.709
It was --
It was a lot.It was too much.

03:51.753 --> 03:54.103
[ Chuckles ]
It's too much.
[ Chuckles ]

03:54.146 --> 03:55.409
Is everything good
with Theo?

03:55.452 --> 03:56.975
Feels like I haven't seen him
in a while.

03:57.019 --> 03:58.150
Oh. Uh, yeah.

03:58.194 --> 03:59.500
He was just doing laundry
last night.

03:59.543 --> 04:01.545
Cool.[ Thunder rumbles ]

04:02.590 --> 04:04.069
Morning.

04:04.113 --> 04:06.028
Hey.
Hey.

04:06.071 --> 04:09.771
♪♪

04:09.814 --> 04:11.294
Jack: Ruiz.

04:11.338 --> 04:13.427
You subbing?

04:14.732 --> 04:19.084
[ Thunder rumbles ]

04:20.434 --> 04:22.305
You didn't tell me
you were subbing today.

04:22.349 --> 04:24.916
You didn't tell me
you were cleared for work.

04:24.960 --> 04:27.789
Yeah. [ Sniffs ]

04:27.832 --> 04:29.225
What's going on, Vic?

04:29.269 --> 04:30.618
I-I don't get it.

04:31.923 --> 04:32.837
I--

04:32.881 --> 04:34.970
My -- My friend died,
Theo.

04:35.013 --> 04:36.624
That's what's going on.

04:36.667 --> 04:41.542
Hey, can we --
are -- are we...

04:41.585 --> 04:42.891
♪♪

04:42.934 --> 04:44.588
Vic, I-I don't know
what's going on.

04:44.632 --> 04:46.416
Look, I just --
Can we just work?

04:46.460 --> 04:48.462
Because I really --
I'm excited to be at work.Yeah.

04:48.505 --> 04:49.550
Yeah.
Can we?

04:49.593 --> 04:51.203
Yeah, okay.
Let's -- Let's work.

04:51.247 --> 04:52.248
Okay.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.554
Beckett:
Line up, please!

04:53.597 --> 04:55.207
Come on, line up!

04:55.251 --> 04:56.818
We have a familiar face
with us today.

04:56.861 --> 04:58.428
Welcome to Lieutenant Ruiz.

04:58.472 --> 05:00.082
[ Applause ]

05:01.823 --> 05:04.260
Hughes is back.
Good to have you back, Hughes.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.262
Hughes has agreed
to desk duty today, all day,

05:06.306 --> 05:07.916
with the exception
of Crisis One calls.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.961
Vic: I didn't agree
to that --Some housekeeping.

05:10.005 --> 05:11.311
Okay.Let's see.

05:11.354 --> 05:12.964
The SFD toy drive's
starting today,

05:13.008 --> 05:15.184
so we'll have more public
stopping by than normal

05:15.227 --> 05:17.534
to drop off their toys
and such, so remember --

05:17.578 --> 05:21.451
please be courteous, be kind,
be here to serve, yeah?

05:21.495 --> 05:23.366
And Sullivan, if you --
if you want a, uh,

05:23.410 --> 05:25.368
sexy photo op,
just call your publicist.

05:25.412 --> 05:26.848
[ Chuckles ]

05:26.891 --> 05:28.589
Now, I'm sure you've all been
hearing the rumors about

05:28.632 --> 05:31.287
McCallister being under
investigation by the department

05:31.331 --> 05:32.810
since the pipeline explosion.

05:32.854 --> 05:35.465
Apparently, he's taking
an early retirement.

05:35.509 --> 05:37.859
What?
I know
there's no love lost there,

05:37.902 --> 05:39.817
but he's still
our former fire chief,

05:39.861 --> 05:42.037
so try not to celebrate
too loudly.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.343
Have they named
a new chief?

05:43.386 --> 05:45.214
Someone's been appointed.
I don't have a name.

05:45.257 --> 05:47.782
All I know
is that we have a lady chief.

05:47.825 --> 05:49.610
What? Seriously?
Oh, my God.

05:49.653 --> 05:51.046
This is huge.Yes, indeed.

05:51.089 --> 05:53.178
The city of Seattle's
first female fire chief.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.267
It's very exciting,
if you're into that kinda thing.

05:55.311 --> 05:56.965
More to the point,
she's gonna be making the rounds

05:57.008 --> 05:58.575
the next few weeks
to each house,

05:58.619 --> 06:01.535
so let's please keep this house
in tip-top shape.

06:01.578 --> 06:02.536
And thank you.

06:02.579 --> 06:04.799
Dismissed.

06:04.842 --> 06:06.888
[ Island Police's "Snow" plays ]

06:10.457 --> 06:15.375
♪ Snow is falling down

06:15.418 --> 06:19.248
♪♪

06:19.291 --> 06:23.426
♪ Staring at a flicker
burning in a streetlight ♪

06:23.470 --> 06:27.604
♪ All the cars
are gonna pass me by ♪

06:27.648 --> 06:31.434
♪ Winter making me remember
what you felt like ♪

06:31.478 --> 06:35.264
♪ Now all I see is snow

06:35.307 --> 06:38.180
♪♪

06:38.223 --> 06:39.442
♪ Snow

06:41.575 --> 06:42.532
[ Sighs ]

06:42.576 --> 06:43.751
♪ Snow

06:43.794 --> 06:45.927
[ Klaxons sound ]

06:45.970 --> 06:49.496
Dispatch: Crisis One requested
to 1163 Forrester Lane.Thank God.

06:49.539 --> 06:51.149
♪♪

06:51.193 --> 06:53.064
Alright.

06:53.108 --> 06:54.631
Ah, crap.

06:54.675 --> 06:57.242
[ Engine starts ]

06:58.592 --> 07:02.160
[ Sirens wailing ]

07:12.432 --> 07:14.521
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:16.087 --> 07:18.133
Hughes,
you sure you're good?

07:18.176 --> 07:19.656
Yeah,
you sure you'regood?

07:19.700 --> 07:21.832
Alright, guys,
so the patient's name is Amy.

07:21.876 --> 07:24.356
Dispatch said she's having
some kind of anxiety attack.

07:24.400 --> 07:25.967
Who called it in?

07:26.010 --> 07:27.577
They didn't say,
so I'm assuming a neighbor,

07:27.621 --> 07:29.231
but it must be
pretty bad.[ Knock on door ]

07:29.274 --> 07:31.494
Hi, this is Seattle FD,
Crisis One.

07:33.104 --> 07:34.062
Go ahead.

07:39.546 --> 07:40.764
Hello?

07:40.808 --> 07:43.637
[ Woman breathing shakily ]

07:44.681 --> 07:47.118
Seattle Fire Department.

07:47.162 --> 07:48.642
Emmett: Amy,
we're from Crisis One.

07:48.685 --> 07:50.121
We're here to help.

07:50.165 --> 07:52.210
Your neighbors
are worried about you.Hey. Hey, Amy.

07:52.254 --> 07:53.777
You look like you're having
a panic attack,

07:53.821 --> 07:54.822
but we can help,
okay?

07:54.865 --> 07:56.301
I-I just need you
to breathe in.

07:56.345 --> 07:58.565
Breathe in for me.
Breathe in for four.

07:58.608 --> 08:01.263
This looks like
a domestic-violence situation.

08:01.306 --> 08:02.525
Yeah, then we need
to call the police.

08:02.569 --> 08:04.701
I need you --
I need you guys to --

08:04.745 --> 08:06.442
I'm sorry.
It's okay.

08:06.486 --> 08:09.184
I need you to --
I-I can't breathe.

08:09.227 --> 08:11.403
Okay, just breathe with me.
Breathe with me, okay?

08:11.447 --> 08:13.536
In for four.
Hold for four.[ Inhales deeply ]

08:13.580 --> 08:15.407
Greg: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa. What's going on here, huh?

08:15.451 --> 08:17.366
Is someone hurt?

08:17.409 --> 08:19.455
[ Baby crying ]Amy, did you
call them?

08:19.499 --> 08:20.717
Gonna go see Mom.

08:20.761 --> 08:23.024
No.Jack: Yeah, no, sir,
uh, we got a call

08:23.067 --> 08:24.547
actually
from your neighbors.

08:24.591 --> 08:26.810
Uh, we're Seattle FD,
and -- and --Okay.

08:26.854 --> 08:28.943
...we heard
that your wife was struggling.Honey.

08:28.986 --> 08:30.988
She has these panic attacks.
Poor thing.

08:31.032 --> 08:33.034
We'll get you
a juice, okay?

08:33.077 --> 08:35.036
[ Crying continues ]Shh. It's okay.
Look, I'm gonna get you a juice.

08:35.079 --> 08:36.951
Look, look, look, look.

08:36.994 --> 08:38.779
Hey, look,
you guys are good to go.

08:38.822 --> 08:40.911
Yeah, she has these
panic attacks, you know?

08:40.955 --> 08:42.173
Uh,
gets a little worked up

08:42.217 --> 08:44.132
when she has
one of these episodes.

08:44.175 --> 08:45.525
You should have seen
what she did to the chandelier

08:45.568 --> 08:46.917
last time this happened.
Right, babe? Remember that?

08:48.963 --> 08:51.356
Hey, you know, Amy, I'm
gonna get you some oxygen.
That'll help, alright?

08:51.400 --> 08:52.575
Vic: You know,
I actually think

08:52.619 --> 08:53.794
we should get you
on the aid car, Amy.

08:53.837 --> 08:54.925
Okay?
Can you stand up?

08:54.969 --> 08:56.579
No.Okay.
Can you --

08:56.623 --> 08:58.233
I just needed to buy some time
because he was getting scary.

08:58.276 --> 08:59.756
I made eggs for dinner
for the baby

08:59.800 --> 09:01.236
and Greg got furious.

09:01.279 --> 09:03.107
I can't leave.Okay.

09:03.151 --> 09:05.283
Amy,
did you call this in?

09:05.327 --> 09:06.546
[ Baby crying ]

09:06.589 --> 09:08.678
If I leave,
he'll take him.

09:08.722 --> 09:09.984
He'll take my baby.

09:10.027 --> 09:12.029
He'll tell them
I'm crazy.

09:12.073 --> 09:13.596
He -- He tells everyone
I'm crazy.

09:13.640 --> 09:14.815
[ Crying ] Mommy.

09:14.858 --> 09:16.643
Amy:
I'll lose my baby.

09:16.686 --> 09:17.992
I can't leave.

09:18.035 --> 09:19.384
Okay.

09:19.428 --> 09:21.038
Okay.

09:27.784 --> 09:30.091
[ Elevator bell dings ]Okay, we should probably

09:30.134 --> 09:31.179
separate the toys
by age group so --

09:31.222 --> 09:32.702
Am I a masochist?

09:32.746 --> 09:34.486
Or not.
Is that it?

09:34.530 --> 09:36.967
I mean,
why do I torture myself

09:37.011 --> 09:38.012
by hanging out here?

09:38.055 --> 09:39.666
You're not
hanging out here.

09:39.709 --> 09:41.232
You're volunteering
because you love us.

09:41.276 --> 09:42.233
We need scissors.

09:42.277 --> 09:44.018
Yes, we do.
[ Chuckles ]

09:44.061 --> 09:47.021
I actually love
spending my days off here.

09:47.064 --> 09:49.197
It's like the house
of the friend

09:49.240 --> 09:51.155
that you had
when you were a kid

09:51.199 --> 09:52.896
whose family
you wished would adopt you.

09:52.940 --> 09:54.332
[ Chuckles ]

09:54.376 --> 09:56.421
You know,
Captain Beckett, uh, announced

09:56.465 --> 09:59.033
that they appointed
a new fire chief.

09:59.076 --> 10:01.731
No name yet,
but it's a woman.

10:01.775 --> 10:03.080
Hot damn.

10:03.124 --> 10:04.516
You a little sad
you weren't the first?

10:04.560 --> 10:05.953
Only a little.

10:05.996 --> 10:07.998
With McCallister gone,
I imagine

10:08.042 --> 10:10.218
they'll be wrapping up
your investigation soon, so...

10:10.261 --> 10:13.613
That piece of absolute dog crap.
He buried the investigation.

10:13.656 --> 10:15.440
I can't for the life of me get
an answer from the department

10:15.484 --> 10:17.355
about when I'll receive word
a year later,

10:17.399 --> 10:18.879
and he's just
sneaking out the back door

10:18.922 --> 10:19.967
before closing my case --
scissors.

10:20.010 --> 10:21.359
Uh-huh.

10:21.403 --> 10:23.187
Well, with any luck,
they'll come to their senses

10:23.231 --> 10:24.972
and give, uh,
Beckett the boot.

10:25.015 --> 10:26.538
Beckett's not
the problem here.

10:26.582 --> 10:28.497
No, but he's certainly
aproblem.

10:28.540 --> 10:30.717
Maybe not for you, Herrera --
[Chuckles] --

10:30.760 --> 10:32.457
but for those of us
who have to work with him.

10:34.677 --> 10:36.418
[ Door opens ]

10:36.461 --> 10:38.638
Tell me again
why the divorce papers

10:38.681 --> 10:40.596
are still
in our freezer.

10:40.640 --> 10:41.641
I don't know.

10:41.684 --> 10:43.207
I just --
I hate the idea

10:43.251 --> 10:46.210
of being somebody
that cuts and runs.

10:46.254 --> 10:48.169
Oh, no. If something
doesn't feel good,

10:48.212 --> 10:49.866
it's healthy
to let it go.

10:50.911 --> 10:53.391
I think
we need more toys.

10:55.742 --> 10:57.265
We definitely
did not need more toys.

10:57.308 --> 10:59.223
Oh. [ Sighs ]

11:00.398 --> 11:02.183
Hi.

11:02.226 --> 11:03.619
Oh, thank you.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.621
Happy holidays.
Thank you.

11:05.665 --> 11:09.625
You didn't strike me as one
to kiss and tell.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.409
Oh, my God.

11:11.453 --> 11:13.107
Did Sullivan
say something?He didn't have to.

11:13.150 --> 11:14.891
Not the first dude
to look at me

11:14.935 --> 11:17.372
like he knows, uh,
I slept with his wife.

11:17.415 --> 11:19.156
Wow.

11:19.200 --> 11:20.723
Okay, you don't have to
sound so proud.

11:22.769 --> 11:25.032
Look,
I'm sorry I told him.

11:25.075 --> 11:27.208
I-I know
you're his boss,

11:27.251 --> 11:29.297
but he was pissing me off,
and I-I said it.

11:29.340 --> 11:30.646
[ Exhales sharply ]

11:30.690 --> 11:32.996
Herrera, if you're using me
to make him jealous

11:33.040 --> 11:35.999
or spice up your situation
or whatever,

11:36.043 --> 11:38.045
I'm totally fine
with it.

11:38.088 --> 11:41.091
Mm-hmm.[ Chuckling ] Okay.

11:41.135 --> 11:43.746
As long as this isn't about
daddy issues.[ Klaxon sounds ]

11:43.790 --> 11:46.793
Engine 19 requested
at 535 Christopher Court.

11:46.836 --> 11:48.098
To be continued.

11:48.142 --> 11:49.621
It's really not.

11:49.665 --> 11:51.711
Yeah, we'll see.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.147
Oh, my God.

11:53.190 --> 11:55.976
[ Sirens wailing, horn honking ]

11:57.804 --> 11:59.414
Hey.

12:01.459 --> 12:03.200
Everything okay?
Yeah.

12:03.244 --> 12:06.421
With -- With me? Yeah.
Yeah, everything's...dope.

12:06.464 --> 12:08.205
Uh-oh.

12:08.249 --> 12:10.381
You only say "dope"
when everything's awful.[ Scoffs ]

12:10.425 --> 12:12.557
Just having a thing.

12:14.211 --> 12:16.779
You wanna
talk to me about it?

12:16.823 --> 12:18.999
I mean,
we're friends, right?

12:19.042 --> 12:20.435
You're Vic's friend.

12:20.478 --> 12:21.958
It's a Vic thing?

12:22.002 --> 12:23.655
Never mind.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.832
Thanks anyway, man.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.967
Call was a car
versus pedestrian --

12:31.011 --> 12:32.795
Oh, my God.

12:32.839 --> 12:36.364
♪♪

12:36.407 --> 12:38.192
Hey, guys.

12:38.235 --> 12:40.368
Ain't no party
like a Christmas party, huh?

12:40.411 --> 12:43.850
♪♪

12:43.893 --> 12:45.242
Jack: Breathe in.

12:45.286 --> 12:46.287
[ Oxygen hissing,
baby cries nearby ]

12:46.330 --> 12:48.202
Okay, Amy,
are you unsafe here?

12:48.245 --> 12:49.725
You can just nod
yes or no.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.335
Baby: [ Wails ] Mommy!

12:51.379 --> 12:52.815
Okay.

12:52.859 --> 12:54.425
[ Crying continues ]

12:54.469 --> 12:57.037
This is outside our purview.
We need to call the police.

12:57.080 --> 12:58.386
Agreed.
I'll take care of it.

12:58.429 --> 13:00.388
Okay.Greg:
Play with that.

13:00.431 --> 13:02.607
[ Baby screaming ]

13:02.651 --> 13:04.871
Hey, listen, guys,
thanks for the help, right,

13:04.914 --> 13:07.351
but you're upsetting
my kid, okay?

13:07.395 --> 13:09.266
Now, she's never
needed oxygen before,

13:09.310 --> 13:10.485
so just get an ice pack,

13:10.528 --> 13:12.313
gonna put it
on the back of her neck,

13:12.356 --> 13:13.314
huh, and we're good.

13:13.357 --> 13:14.924
You're good, right, babe?

13:14.968 --> 13:16.926
Amy:
Yeah. Yeah.

13:16.970 --> 13:19.973
We-- We-- We're good.
Thank you.Baby: Mommy!

13:20.016 --> 13:21.583
I'm -- I'm -- I'm good.
Thank you.

13:21.626 --> 13:23.585
Thank you, guys.
We're fine. You can leave.

13:23.628 --> 13:25.456
I-I'm just such a wreck
at the holidays.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.241
Yeah. Tough to live with,
but I sure do love her.

13:28.590 --> 13:30.244
Amy.
Amy, come on.

13:30.287 --> 13:31.680
Let's go.Whoa. What the hell
are you doing?
Hughes --

13:31.723 --> 13:32.899
What the hell are you doing?
Sit down.

13:32.942 --> 13:34.465
What the hell are you doing?
Put him down.

13:34.509 --> 13:35.771
Let's go.Are you nuts?

13:35.815 --> 13:36.816
Please stop.
Vic.

13:36.859 --> 13:38.252
Put my kid down!Amy --

13:38.295 --> 13:39.688
That's it. That's it.
I'm calling the cops.

13:39.731 --> 13:41.211
Vic:
It's okay.

13:41.255 --> 13:42.778
Vic,
what are you doing?

13:42.822 --> 13:44.519
Baby: [ Whining ] Mommy.Greg: Yes, hi.

13:44.562 --> 13:45.781
Vic.I'd like to report
an attempted kidnapping

13:45.825 --> 13:46.738
in my home.

13:46.782 --> 13:49.132
Baby: [ Sobs ] Mommy.

13:52.962 --> 13:55.312
We don't move the car,
we do not move anything.

13:55.356 --> 13:57.445
Right now, that car
is crushing his lower body,

13:57.488 --> 14:00.317
but it's also pressing against
all of his internal injuries.

14:00.361 --> 14:01.449
The minute we move it,
he's gonna start to bleed out.

14:01.492 --> 14:03.320
How fast?
Real fast.

14:03.364 --> 14:05.627
Likely, his intestines,
kidneys, and liver.

14:05.670 --> 14:07.542
He'll be in cardiac arrest
before we know it.

14:07.585 --> 14:09.457
Beckett: Bishop,
you need to turn the car off

14:09.500 --> 14:11.981
and -- and press down
on the emergency brake.

14:12.025 --> 14:14.418
Sullivan, hold on to her so that
she does not rock the car.

14:14.462 --> 14:16.725
Alright? And the instant
she puts that brake on,

14:16.768 --> 14:18.596
get the chock blocks
thrown underneath the tires.

14:18.640 --> 14:20.076
Who's calling
the shots today, Warren?

14:21.251 --> 14:23.906
Captain, right now,
he's stable,

14:23.950 --> 14:25.690
but if we move that car
even an inch

14:25.734 --> 14:27.823
without the proper
medical equipment, he
will die on the spot.

14:27.867 --> 14:29.042
I'm aware
of the stakes, Warren.

14:31.522 --> 14:32.959
Gentle.[ Clicking ]

14:33.002 --> 14:34.351
Got it.
Alright.

14:34.395 --> 14:35.483
Ben: Alright, good.
Montgomery, I'm gonna need you

14:35.526 --> 14:37.093
to climb up top
and secure from above.

14:37.137 --> 14:38.790
Okay.Climb on top of this car

14:38.834 --> 14:40.140
because it's not the one
pushing into his abdomen.Copy.

14:40.183 --> 14:41.706
Alright.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.012
We were having
an early Christmas dinner

14:43.056 --> 14:44.318
at my mother-in-law's today,

14:44.361 --> 14:46.363
and it was all systems go
this morning.

14:46.407 --> 14:47.451
Any of you got kids?

14:47.495 --> 14:48.975
Yeah,
I got two boys at home,

14:49.018 --> 14:50.193
and a little girl
we, um...

14:50.237 --> 14:52.543
Well, then,
you know what it's like.

14:52.587 --> 14:54.371
I've got three,
as well.

14:54.415 --> 14:56.808
My wife was up this morning
running around

14:56.852 --> 14:58.810
wrapping
and hiding presents

14:58.854 --> 15:01.161
while my oldest daughter
was having a meltdown

15:01.204 --> 15:02.727
over a guy she likes.[ Chuckles ]

15:02.771 --> 15:05.687
Who commented a heart emoji
under her picture.

15:05.730 --> 15:06.993
One of my twin boys

15:07.036 --> 15:08.820
kept throwing a football
at the other,

15:08.864 --> 15:11.432
even though he knows
that's not his brother's thing.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.608
And we all
raced out of the house

15:13.651 --> 15:15.827
to the other side of town,

15:15.871 --> 15:18.395
and we ordered
last-minute groceries.

15:18.439 --> 15:19.875
When we got there,

15:19.919 --> 15:23.183
I realized that I accidentally
put in our home address.

15:23.226 --> 15:26.186
No way my kids were gonna go
without their egg nog.

15:26.229 --> 15:27.839
Gotta have the egg nog.

15:27.883 --> 15:30.451
Gotta have the egg nog.
[ Chuckles ]

15:30.494 --> 15:32.757
[ Grunting ]

15:32.801 --> 15:34.237
Feeling a lot of pain?

15:34.281 --> 15:37.110
Surprisingly,
not as much as you'd think.

15:37.153 --> 15:39.199
Yeah, well,
that's the adrenaline talking.

15:39.242 --> 15:40.374
Can you feel
your legs?

15:40.417 --> 15:41.549
Yeah.

15:41.592 --> 15:43.116
Can you move your toes
inside your shoes?

15:43.159 --> 15:45.553
Yeah, I can.
That's good, right?

15:45.596 --> 15:46.989
Yes, it's good.

15:47.033 --> 15:49.035
[ Laughs ]

15:49.078 --> 15:51.167
I'm sorry.

15:51.211 --> 15:54.344
I, uh --
I laugh when I'm nervous.

15:54.388 --> 15:58.000
Anyway, I run back over here
to grab the groceries,

15:58.044 --> 16:00.002
and they'd left them all
in the driveway.

16:00.046 --> 16:03.614
So, I park the truck up top,
run down,

16:03.658 --> 16:06.530
but before I can even
pick up a bag -- bam.

16:06.574 --> 16:08.010
[ Machine beeps ]

16:08.054 --> 16:10.143
I meant to get
my brakes checked last week.

16:10.186 --> 16:11.361
They were squeaking.

16:11.405 --> 16:13.407
[ Grunts ]

16:13.450 --> 16:16.236
My wife always tells me

16:16.279 --> 16:17.759
push the parking brake
when I park.

16:17.802 --> 16:19.500
I should listen to her more.

16:19.543 --> 16:21.241
That's universally sound
advice, my man.

16:21.284 --> 16:23.112
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

16:23.156 --> 16:24.679
That your wife?

16:24.722 --> 16:26.028
You should answer it.

16:27.638 --> 16:29.336
It'll just worry her.

16:29.379 --> 16:31.120
Eh, she'd rather know.
Trust me.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.818
♪♪

16:33.862 --> 16:35.385
Montgomery,
take over for me here.

16:35.429 --> 16:36.299
Yeah, I got you.

16:37.474 --> 16:41.783
♪♪

16:41.826 --> 16:44.438
I'm not letting that man die
a week before Christmas.

16:44.481 --> 16:46.614
I'm not letting that man's kids
come home to a dead dad.

16:46.657 --> 16:48.529
Not again.
We need the PRT.

16:48.572 --> 16:50.748
Your knife-mobile?It's his only chance
for survival.

16:50.792 --> 16:52.663
Look, if I have the PRT,
some blood,

16:52.707 --> 16:54.056
and another set of hands,
maybe I can save him.

16:54.100 --> 16:56.058
I can't authorize the PRT,
Warren.

16:56.102 --> 16:57.929
Well,
call somebody who can.

16:57.973 --> 17:00.584
Hey, hey, we have a new chief,
right? Call her.

17:00.628 --> 17:03.109
Tell her the man is gonna die
unless we have the PRT.

17:03.152 --> 17:05.154
She'll be happy
to have a feel-good story

17:05.198 --> 17:06.460
on her first day.

17:06.503 --> 17:08.157
Leave it to Fire Zaddy
to find the PR angle.

17:08.201 --> 17:10.203
He's right.
It's our best shot.

17:10.246 --> 17:12.205
I'm gonna call Miranda
to have the blood ready.

17:12.248 --> 17:13.336
You get
the PRT approved.[ Cellphone unlocks ]

17:13.380 --> 17:15.121
I'm not
making any promises.

17:15.164 --> 17:17.558
Carina's at the station
if you need some extra hands.

17:17.601 --> 17:18.994
Yes. Yes.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.778
[ Ringing ]

17:20.822 --> 17:22.389
[ Baby crying ]

17:22.432 --> 17:23.868
The cops are coming.
You wanna give me my kid?

17:25.174 --> 17:26.871
Do you wanna
give me my kid?
Amy.

17:26.915 --> 17:28.656
Amy, all you have to do
is come with us.

17:28.699 --> 17:31.441
You're scaring him.No,
you'rescaring him!

17:31.485 --> 17:33.487
Hughes, Hughes, what the hell
are you doing?You're also
scaring your wife.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.228
She's obviously
terrified of you.
Did you
tell her that?

17:35.271 --> 17:36.620
No.
No, of course not.

17:36.664 --> 17:38.448
Um, please, just leave.
We're fine.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.842
The police are on their way,
okay?
Hughes --

17:40.885 --> 17:42.800
[ Watch beeping ]I'm not gonna leave him here
to terrorize his family!

17:42.844 --> 17:43.975
Hughes.What's that noise?

17:44.019 --> 17:45.977
Outside. Now.

17:46.021 --> 17:47.631
What the hell
is that noise?

17:47.675 --> 17:49.329
Hughes. Hughes.

17:49.372 --> 17:50.156
Vic: Okay.Hughes.

17:50.199 --> 17:52.593
Now.

17:52.636 --> 17:54.377
[ Breathing shakily ]Please,
just give him back.

17:54.421 --> 17:56.640
Baby:
[ Crying ] Mommy.

17:56.684 --> 17:58.207
Come on.
Come on.

17:58.251 --> 18:00.644
I know.
I know.
Okay. Okay.

18:00.688 --> 18:02.168
I know.

18:02.211 --> 18:03.386
[ Gasping ]

18:03.430 --> 18:04.735
Okay.

18:04.779 --> 18:06.259
Okay.

18:06.302 --> 18:07.738
It's okay.

18:07.782 --> 18:10.132
Please.

18:10.176 --> 18:12.178
It's okay. It's okay.
I got you.

18:12.221 --> 18:14.397
[ Sirens approach ]Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

18:14.441 --> 18:16.138
Oh. Oh.

18:16.182 --> 18:17.966
Oh. Oh.

18:18.009 --> 18:21.012
[ Sirens stop ]

18:21.056 --> 18:22.971
[ Car doors open, close ]

18:23.014 --> 18:28.585
♪♪

18:28.629 --> 18:31.806
[ Police radio chatter ]

18:31.849 --> 18:34.461
[ Breathing shakily ]

18:34.504 --> 18:41.337
♪♪

18:45.602 --> 18:48.692
[ Sighs ] Come on, Beckett.
Come on.

18:48.736 --> 18:51.521
This is
a highly unique situation.

18:51.565 --> 18:53.915
Can you please
just approve this for us?

18:53.958 --> 18:54.916
Just give it
to me straight.

18:54.959 --> 18:57.092
The facts.

19:00.487 --> 19:03.316
This car is pressing against
your abdomen and pelvis,

19:03.359 --> 19:04.621
and when we move this car,

19:04.665 --> 19:06.232
your body will succumb
to the injuries,

19:06.275 --> 19:08.364
and I will have minutes to try
to stop the bleeding,

19:08.408 --> 19:11.280
but we are working on
a solution.

19:11.324 --> 19:12.281
So, until then,
we just have --

19:12.325 --> 19:13.891
Just wait.

19:13.935 --> 19:16.242
Yeah.

19:16.285 --> 19:20.289
Okay, I'm officially tipping
into panic mode,

19:20.333 --> 19:22.204
and I'm not my best
when I'm panicked,

19:22.248 --> 19:23.597
so someone tell me

19:23.640 --> 19:24.989
your funniest Christmas story
or something.

19:27.557 --> 19:31.039
[ Chuckles ]
No, no, no.

19:31.082 --> 19:32.649
I --
Okay, I got one.
No.

19:32.693 --> 19:34.738
So, there was
this one time, I, uh --

19:34.782 --> 19:36.392
I came home
Christmas morning.

19:36.436 --> 19:38.612
Don't do it.
I-I lived
with a roommate,

19:38.655 --> 19:40.396
and his boyfriend
was over a lot --

19:40.440 --> 19:41.571
Please stop.
And, uh --

19:41.615 --> 19:43.138
No, don't stop.
Don't stop.

19:43.182 --> 19:44.705
[ Chuckles ]
And when I got there,

19:44.748 --> 19:46.794
my roommate was setting up
Christmas brunch,

19:46.837 --> 19:49.231
and you know, I'm like,
"Hey, Merry Christmas,"

19:49.275 --> 19:50.493
and then I hear
from down the hallway --

19:50.537 --> 19:52.016
Oh, God, kill me.

19:52.060 --> 19:53.366
"I have some bells
you can jingle."

19:53.409 --> 19:55.411
No.
[ Laughs ]

19:55.455 --> 19:57.805
Actually,
it was, "Ho, ho, ho.

19:57.848 --> 19:59.459
Come jingle my bells."

19:59.502 --> 20:01.025
[ Laughter ]

20:01.069 --> 20:02.940
Please tell me
he was wearing --

20:02.984 --> 20:04.812
A Santa hat
and nothing else.

20:04.855 --> 20:06.292
[ Chuckles ]
Where was the hat?

20:06.335 --> 20:07.641
Not where
you want it to be.

20:07.684 --> 20:08.946
Why'd you
come over unannounced?!

20:08.990 --> 20:10.992
Bro,
I lived there.
Right.

20:11.035 --> 20:12.515
[ Laughter ]

20:12.559 --> 20:16.040
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

20:16.084 --> 20:20.001
Terrence, she --
she has time to get here.

20:20.044 --> 20:22.395
I think you should answer
that phone.

20:22.438 --> 20:25.224
[ Buzzing continues ]

20:25.267 --> 20:28.792
We're supposed to
go caroling this weekend.

20:28.836 --> 20:33.144
I swear,
when that woman sings...

20:33.188 --> 20:39.238
her voice, her smile,
her whatever,

20:39.281 --> 20:43.503
she always
makes me feel better.

20:43.546 --> 20:44.982
No matter what.

20:45.026 --> 20:46.201
[ Buzzing continues ]

20:46.245 --> 20:49.552
Then you have to
be brave now.

20:49.596 --> 20:51.989
Give her the respect
she deserves.

20:52.033 --> 20:54.992
[ Buzzing continues ]

20:55.036 --> 20:59.606
♪♪

20:59.649 --> 21:02.130
[ Clears throat ]

21:02.173 --> 21:04.001
Hey, honey.

21:04.045 --> 21:08.658
Okay, listen,
I love you.

21:08.702 --> 21:09.964
Just try
not to freak out, okay?

21:10.007 --> 21:11.879
I don't want you
to scare the kids.

21:11.922 --> 21:15.361
So, try and just listen,
okay?

21:15.404 --> 21:17.537
Screw it.
I'm getting the PRT.

21:17.580 --> 21:19.800
♪♪

21:19.843 --> 21:21.628
[ Elevator bell dings ]Andy: Alright,
here we go.

21:21.671 --> 21:23.325
Eh, so,
how does it work?

21:23.369 --> 21:25.806
Do people come here
and pick out toys?

21:25.849 --> 21:27.373
Uh, no,
right before Christmas,

21:27.416 --> 21:29.244
we, um --
we go around town,

21:29.288 --> 21:31.594
drop them off at hospitals,
shelters,

21:31.638 --> 21:33.204
you know, places where kids

21:33.248 --> 21:35.076
might not get a present
this year.Nice.

21:35.119 --> 21:35.990
Can I come?

21:37.296 --> 21:38.862
Yeah.

21:40.037 --> 21:41.996
I-I think
it's my mom.

21:42.039 --> 21:43.214
I...

21:43.258 --> 21:45.826
I'm afraid
to file the papers

21:45.869 --> 21:49.395
because then that means
I cut and run like my mom,

21:49.438 --> 21:53.050
and -- and it sounds so dumb
to say out loud.

21:53.094 --> 21:55.357
Like, "Oh, boo-hoo,
my parents wounded me

21:55.401 --> 21:57.098
and all my problems
are because of them."

21:57.141 --> 21:59.318
It doesn't sound dumb
at all.

21:59.361 --> 22:00.971
Well, you're not special.

22:01.015 --> 22:02.408
[ Sighs ]

22:02.451 --> 22:05.454
We're all just undoing
what our parents did to us.

22:05.498 --> 22:06.586
Okay, well,
if you're so wise,

22:06.629 --> 22:09.023
why haven't you
and Maya told anyone

22:09.066 --> 22:10.981
that you're gonna
have a baby?

22:11.025 --> 22:13.114
Because there is
no baby yet.

22:13.157 --> 22:15.159
There is
not even sperm yet.

22:15.203 --> 22:16.639
Ah, you're afraid

22:16.683 --> 22:20.208
she's gonna change her mind,
aren't you?

22:20.251 --> 22:22.732
She has massive walls
around her heart.

22:22.776 --> 22:24.821
And she's
taking them down.

22:24.865 --> 22:26.170
Brick by brick.

22:26.214 --> 22:28.042
[ Cellphone ringing ]For you.

22:28.085 --> 22:29.696
Hey, Warren,
what's up?

22:29.739 --> 22:31.350
Yeah,
she's still here.

22:31.393 --> 22:32.873
Hey, Warren.

22:32.916 --> 22:34.570
Come with me.

22:34.614 --> 22:37.704
Yeah? Okay.

22:37.747 --> 22:40.271
I hope Delilah's not speeding.

22:40.315 --> 22:41.795
[ Coughing ]

22:41.838 --> 22:44.754
Travis: Okay.
Hold on. I got you.Theo: Oh. Hey.

22:44.798 --> 22:46.060
This is freaking brutal.

22:46.103 --> 22:47.496
There's nothing
we can do?

22:47.540 --> 22:49.411
There has to be something
that we can do.

22:49.455 --> 22:51.195
Okay, well,
we're gonna keep him alive

22:51.239 --> 22:53.502
so he can say goodbye
to his wife.

22:53.546 --> 22:54.764
That's what we can do.

22:54.808 --> 22:58.115
No. No.

22:58.159 --> 23:00.379
You need
to make this happen now.

23:00.422 --> 23:01.989
Thank you, Bishop,
for telling me how to do my job.

23:02.032 --> 23:03.425
I keep getting
the run-around.

23:03.469 --> 23:04.600
Ben:
Doesn't matter.

23:04.644 --> 23:06.210
Herrera's on the way
with the PRT.

23:06.254 --> 23:07.690
So is DeLuca,
who can assist.

23:07.734 --> 23:09.475
Warren,
this is not how this goes.It is today.

23:09.518 --> 23:11.172
Look,
suspend me if you want,

23:11.215 --> 23:13.043
but not until after
I save this man's life.

23:13.087 --> 23:15.785
♪♪

23:15.829 --> 23:18.222
Terrence.
I have good news.

23:18.266 --> 23:20.573
We're getting a vehicle here
called the PRT.

23:20.616 --> 23:22.270
It's basically
a mobile operating room.

23:22.313 --> 23:23.750
What'll you
have to do?

23:23.793 --> 23:25.186
Well, first,
a group of us

23:25.229 --> 23:27.144
are gonna get this vehicle
off of you.

23:27.188 --> 23:28.624
W-W-Won't that make me
bleed out?

23:28.668 --> 23:29.843
That's what
you said earlier.

23:29.886 --> 23:31.410
We'll move you quickly
into the PRT

23:31.453 --> 23:32.541
and we'll do CPR
if we need to.

23:32.585 --> 23:34.064
We'll give you blood.

23:34.108 --> 23:35.979
And I will perform
what is called a thoracotomy.

23:36.023 --> 23:37.459
I'm gonna operate
on your chest

23:37.503 --> 23:39.635
to clamp the blood flow
to the lower part of your body

23:39.679 --> 23:41.420
so that you don't
bleed out.

23:41.463 --> 23:42.508
Sounds easy.

23:44.423 --> 23:46.729
They let you do all that
as a firefighter?

23:46.773 --> 23:49.689
Well, I'm also a surgeon.My man.

23:49.732 --> 23:52.648
[ Tires screech ]

23:52.692 --> 24:00.395
♪♪

24:00.439 --> 24:02.571
How did this happen?!

24:02.615 --> 24:03.659
Travis: Slow.
Ben: Ma'am.

24:03.703 --> 24:04.660
Slow down.
Slow down.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.880
Why is this car
still on him?!

24:06.923 --> 24:08.795
What are
all of you doing?!

24:08.838 --> 24:10.449
Honey, honey, listen.

24:10.492 --> 24:12.146
These people are doing

24:12.189 --> 24:13.974
everything
that they can, okay?

24:14.017 --> 24:16.280
And soon, they're gonna push
this car off me,

24:16.324 --> 24:18.631
and when they do...
there's a chance --

24:18.674 --> 24:22.199
No. No. No.
Stop.

24:22.243 --> 24:24.375
I-I cannot lose you.

24:24.419 --> 24:27.074
You came back for egg nog.
Egg nog.

24:27.117 --> 24:29.511
Honey, I need you to listen
to what I'm about to say.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.600
And please don't stop me.

24:31.644 --> 24:33.297
Let me finish, okay?

24:33.341 --> 24:35.604
Because I'm a little scared,

24:35.648 --> 24:37.867
and I need to say this.

24:37.911 --> 24:39.739
Tell Penelope
that no matter

24:39.782 --> 24:41.915
how many boys
comment on her photos,

24:41.958 --> 24:44.483
that her love
starts with her herself,

24:44.526 --> 24:45.701
and that way,

24:45.745 --> 24:47.529
she's always got a place
to come home to...

24:47.573 --> 24:48.791
[ Sobbing ]...when times get hard.

24:48.835 --> 24:50.140
Alright?

24:50.184 --> 24:52.795
Tell Rory
to be good to his brother.

24:52.839 --> 24:56.190
He needs to embrace
the fact that --

24:56.233 --> 24:58.192
that Tommy's
favorite color is pink

24:58.235 --> 25:01.456
and that he --
he idolizes Janet Jackson, okay?

25:01.500 --> 25:02.588
Because there are gonna be

25:02.631 --> 25:04.938
enough people
that give him a hard time,

25:04.981 --> 25:08.245
and his brother
cannot be one of them.

25:08.289 --> 25:11.684
Tell them to dream big

25:11.727 --> 25:14.730
and to --
to love boldly, okay?Mm-hmm.

25:14.774 --> 25:16.602
And most importantly,

25:16.645 --> 25:19.474
tell them that no matter
where this life takes them,

25:19.518 --> 25:21.389
that I'll be right there
with them,

25:21.432 --> 25:23.173
every step of the way.

25:23.217 --> 25:25.959
And please,
please don't let them

25:26.002 --> 25:27.569
grow up
to hate Christmas.

25:27.613 --> 25:29.963
[ Sirens approach ]Because we're Tillermans,

25:30.006 --> 25:32.966
and we love Christmas,
okay?

25:33.009 --> 25:34.576
[ Sobbing ] Okay.Beckett: Warren!

25:34.620 --> 25:36.883
Good news!
PRT's approved.

25:36.926 --> 25:39.581
[ Siren continues ]

25:39.625 --> 25:41.104
I was doing this
either way.

25:41.148 --> 25:46.370
♪♪

25:51.680 --> 25:52.725
[ Sighs ]
You don't need to do this.

25:52.768 --> 25:55.162
Well,
Gibson says I do.

25:55.205 --> 25:58.513
♪♪

25:58.557 --> 25:59.949
Okay.

25:59.993 --> 26:01.864
[ Police radio chatter ]

26:01.908 --> 26:03.997
♪♪

26:04.040 --> 26:05.520
What happened?

26:05.564 --> 26:07.478
Police found
multiple bruises on Amy,

26:07.522 --> 26:08.697
so they're
taking him in.

26:08.741 --> 26:09.742
[ Car door closes ]

26:09.785 --> 26:11.482
But first,
I had to convince them

26:11.526 --> 26:14.355
that Greg was in fact
the bad guy and not you.

26:14.398 --> 26:17.097
We should have been doing
crisis intervention.

26:17.140 --> 26:18.577
And, Hughes,
what you did in there --

26:18.620 --> 26:19.882
Yeah, I know.
I know.
No,
you don't know,

26:19.926 --> 26:21.188
because if you knew,
you wouldn't have done it.

26:21.231 --> 26:22.537
Our job is to help people.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.931
What you did was put
that entire family at risk.

26:24.974 --> 26:26.193
I think the family
was already at risk.

26:26.236 --> 26:28.238
How is Amy?
Is she alright?

26:28.282 --> 26:29.718
No, she's pretty shaken up,
actually.

26:31.198 --> 26:32.199
Hughes, stop.

26:32.242 --> 26:33.766
I left my heart monitor
in there.

26:33.809 --> 26:35.115
No,
I will get it for you.I have to
at least apologize.

26:35.158 --> 26:36.682
Hughes, stop!

26:36.725 --> 26:38.858
[ Knock on door ]

26:40.990 --> 26:41.948
Amy?

26:41.991 --> 26:44.385
It's Vic, the firefighter.

26:44.428 --> 26:48.563
I for-- Uh, I forgot my watch --
my watch thing.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.130
[ Door unlocks ]

26:52.567 --> 26:53.524
You...

26:53.568 --> 26:56.092
I-I am sorry.

26:56.136 --> 26:58.442
I was trying to help,
and --

26:58.486 --> 26:59.661
You could've
gotten us killed.
Yeah.

27:01.358 --> 27:04.057
Can I...so...

27:06.929 --> 27:09.628
Thank you.

27:11.194 --> 27:12.152
[ Baby giggling ]

27:12.195 --> 27:13.675
I saw they took him in.

27:13.719 --> 27:15.024
Amy: Yeah.

27:15.068 --> 27:16.286
Just for the night,
until he calms down,

27:16.330 --> 27:18.724
but he'll be more pissed
when he gets home.

27:18.767 --> 27:20.247
Okay.

27:22.292 --> 27:23.424
Okay,
let's get you packed.

27:23.467 --> 27:25.295
What?

27:25.339 --> 27:27.950
I-I can sit with him
or I can pack for you.

27:27.994 --> 27:29.473
Which do you prefer?I can't leave.

27:29.517 --> 27:30.561
You can't stay.

27:30.605 --> 27:31.780
You don't understand.

27:31.824 --> 27:33.782
He owns everything.

27:33.826 --> 27:35.610
He controls everything.

27:35.654 --> 27:37.830
I come from nothing.

27:37.873 --> 27:39.788
I've tried.

27:39.832 --> 27:41.007
He threatens me
with lawyers.

27:41.050 --> 27:44.053
He tells everyone
I'm crazy.

27:44.097 --> 27:46.534
Well -- Uh, do you --
do you have anyone --

27:46.577 --> 27:49.711
anyone he doesn't
know about, or...

27:49.755 --> 27:53.280
I-I have a cousin
in Portland.

27:53.323 --> 27:54.760
Okay, great.
You call your cousin,

27:54.803 --> 27:56.152
and then you're gonna
call the police

27:56.196 --> 27:57.414
and tell them
you want to press charges

27:57.458 --> 27:58.807
so they can keep him
longer than overnight,

27:58.851 --> 28:01.244
and then we're gonna pack.

28:01.288 --> 28:03.943
I-I know
I-I did not help earlier,

28:03.986 --> 28:05.596
but I am here
to help now.

28:05.640 --> 28:08.382
You are staying here
because you love your son

28:08.425 --> 28:09.731
and you want to
protect him,

28:09.775 --> 28:12.386
and I get that,
but if you really --

28:12.429 --> 28:14.475
if you really
want to protect him,

28:14.518 --> 28:15.432
you have to leave.

28:17.304 --> 28:21.221
If your son is not safe
from his father...

28:21.264 --> 28:22.744
Amy, if you are not safe
from his father,

28:22.788 --> 28:25.747
then it is time
to leave.

28:25.791 --> 28:27.706
Amy. Amy.

28:29.795 --> 28:32.188
It's -- It's time to leave.

28:32.232 --> 28:38.368
♪♪

28:38.412 --> 28:39.587
Okay.

28:41.545 --> 28:45.071
I have a suitcase
in the closet upstairs.

28:45.114 --> 28:46.202
Okay.

28:46.246 --> 28:54.950
♪♪

28:54.994 --> 28:56.952
[ Baby cooing ]

28:56.996 --> 28:59.955
♪♪

28:59.999 --> 29:01.391
I prepped
as much as I could.

29:01.435 --> 29:02.523
Set up
your thoracotomy kit.

29:02.566 --> 29:03.524
Thank you.

29:03.567 --> 29:05.091
♪♪

29:05.134 --> 29:06.135
Will you sing for me?

29:06.179 --> 29:07.354
Baby.

29:07.397 --> 29:09.486
Please.

29:09.530 --> 29:15.231
♪♪

29:15.275 --> 29:20.367
♪ O holy night

29:20.410 --> 29:26.547
♪ The stars
are brightly shining ♪

29:26.590 --> 29:29.680
♪ It is the night

29:29.724 --> 29:35.556
♪ Of our dear Savior's birth

29:35.599 --> 29:40.387
Both:
♪ Long lay the world

29:40.430 --> 29:47.046
♪ In sin and error pining

29:47.089 --> 29:51.267
♪ 'Til he appear'd

29:51.311 --> 29:53.269
♪ And the soul felt...

29:53.313 --> 29:56.620
Delilah, Terrence.
It's -- It's time.

29:56.664 --> 29:58.448
[ Breathing shakily ]

29:58.492 --> 30:00.581
Terrence:
Turn your back, baby.

30:00.624 --> 30:02.496
I don't want you
to see this.No!

30:02.539 --> 30:07.588
I don't want to --But please keep singing.

30:07.631 --> 30:10.373
No.Come right over here.
You just sit right over here.

30:10.417 --> 30:11.810
I love you.

30:11.853 --> 30:14.029
I love you, too, baby.

30:15.335 --> 30:17.467
I'm gonna do
everything in my power.Thank you.

30:17.511 --> 30:18.294
I promise.
Thank you.

30:21.689 --> 30:24.866
-Okay, hands around.
-I'm ready.

30:24.910 --> 30:29.610
♪ Fall on

30:29.653 --> 30:31.525
♪ Your knees

30:31.568 --> 30:33.048
Ben: On my count.

30:33.092 --> 30:40.229
One, two, three!♪ O hear the angel voices

30:40.273 --> 30:41.709
[ Grunting ]

30:41.752 --> 30:49.717
♪ O night divine

30:49.760 --> 30:52.720
♪ O night

30:52.763 --> 30:56.376
♪ When Christ was born

30:56.419 --> 30:59.118
♪ O night...

30:59.161 --> 31:00.510
Young woman: Mom?

31:00.554 --> 31:04.297
♪ Divine

31:04.340 --> 31:08.910
♪ O, O night divine

31:08.954 --> 31:10.912
[ Flatlining ]

31:10.956 --> 31:17.136
♪ Fall on your knees

31:17.179 --> 31:24.795
♪ O hear the angel voices

31:24.839 --> 31:30.410
♪ O night divine

31:30.453 --> 31:35.676
♪ O, O night divine

31:35.719 --> 31:37.199
[ Alarm beeping ]

31:37.243 --> 31:38.200
Ben: Okay.

31:38.244 --> 31:39.810
Yeah.
I clamped the aorta.

31:39.854 --> 31:41.943
It's time to go.
We gotta move.
Yeah.

31:41.987 --> 31:43.379
Tell Herrera to drive us
to Grey-Sloan.

31:43.423 --> 31:44.424
While he's still open?

31:44.467 --> 31:45.947
He's in
cardiac arrest.

31:45.991 --> 31:48.297
Tell her not to speed.
Alright, nice and slow.

31:48.341 --> 31:50.125
It's his only shot.[ Radio clicks ]

31:50.169 --> 31:52.084
Herrera,
we gotta get to the hospital.

31:52.127 --> 31:53.737
Excuse me. Copy.
On my way.

31:53.781 --> 31:54.782
En route to Grey-Sloan.

31:54.825 --> 31:57.437
I'm coming.

31:57.480 --> 32:00.222
Delilah:
What does that mean?

32:01.832 --> 32:04.226
What does that mean?

32:04.270 --> 32:06.228
[ Engine starts ]

32:07.708 --> 32:09.318
[ Siren wailing ]What does that mean?

32:09.362 --> 32:12.365
That siren
means life, okay?

32:12.408 --> 32:14.802
In this situation,
at this moment,

32:14.845 --> 32:16.978
that siren
means he's alive.

32:17.022 --> 32:18.980
[ Laughing ]

32:19.024 --> 32:21.765
Let's go.
Let's go.

32:21.809 --> 32:23.550
Thank you!

32:23.593 --> 32:26.292
Thank you so much.

32:26.335 --> 32:28.816
Oh.

32:28.859 --> 32:36.128
♪♪

32:40.393 --> 32:43.439
Hughes.
You're benched.Fine.

32:43.483 --> 32:44.788
I'm serious.

32:44.832 --> 32:46.181
Yep. Me too.

32:46.225 --> 32:48.183
You disobeyed orders today --
twice.

32:48.227 --> 32:50.446
You put the department
and the program in jeopardy.

32:50.490 --> 32:52.709
Yeah, I heard you, Gibson.
I'm on desk duty. I got it.

32:52.753 --> 32:54.363
No, no, not desk duty.
You're benched.

32:54.407 --> 32:56.278
Go home. You're done this shift.
You're out the next two.

32:56.322 --> 32:57.845
Oh, h-hold on.
You are not the Captain.

32:57.888 --> 32:59.107
You can't tell me
to do that.

32:59.151 --> 33:00.891
I'll inform Beckett myself.
You're not okay.

33:00.935 --> 33:03.590
Is this --
Is this punishment

33:03.633 --> 33:05.374
for what happened
at my place?
No, Hughes.

33:05.418 --> 33:06.636
Is that what you --
No.

33:06.680 --> 33:08.160
It has nothing to do
with that.
Okay.

33:08.203 --> 33:09.900
Or you know what?
Actually, yeah, it does,

33:09.944 --> 33:12.468
because it's further proof
that your judgement is just --

33:12.512 --> 33:13.643
Oh, myjudgement?

33:13.687 --> 33:14.993
Yeah.
My --

33:15.036 --> 33:16.603
That's --
That's hilarious.No, no.

33:16.646 --> 33:17.996
We're not --
I'm not
dealing with this.

33:18.039 --> 33:19.606
I don't want to fight
with you, Vic.Okay.

33:19.649 --> 33:21.216
I understand
that you're hurting,

33:21.260 --> 33:22.522
that you're angry.
I get that, okay?

33:22.565 --> 33:24.176
But you can't be like that
out in the field.

33:24.219 --> 33:25.394
You especially
can't be like that

33:25.438 --> 33:26.569
on a Crisis One call.

33:26.613 --> 33:28.397
Hughes.
What? What?

33:28.441 --> 33:31.270
This program
that you fought for

33:31.313 --> 33:33.663
is all we have left of him.

33:33.707 --> 33:35.578
♪♪

33:35.622 --> 33:37.189
You know what?

33:37.232 --> 33:39.495
You can sabotage your life.
I don't -- I don't care,

33:39.539 --> 33:41.323
but I'm not gonna let you
take down his legacy.

33:41.367 --> 33:43.282
Go home.

33:43.325 --> 33:44.761
[ Pounds wall ]

33:44.805 --> 33:50.811
♪♪

33:50.854 --> 33:53.553
[ Breathing shakily ]

33:53.596 --> 33:56.164
♪♪

33:56.208 --> 33:58.514
[ Radio clicks ]Dispatch,
this is PRT 19,

33:58.558 --> 34:00.125
heading back
to the station.

34:00.168 --> 34:03.389
Dispatch: Copy.
Thank you, PRT 19.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.391
You know
what I realized today?

34:07.262 --> 34:08.350
You and I --

34:08.394 --> 34:10.178
we didn't
make each other happy.

34:10.222 --> 34:12.833
[ Scoffs ]
You just realized that?

34:12.876 --> 34:15.009
I mean,
not just this past year,

34:15.053 --> 34:17.011
but when we were together...
at our best.

34:17.055 --> 34:19.318
We were always
sort of...

34:19.361 --> 34:21.015
Fraught.
Exactly.

34:21.059 --> 34:23.278
It was never easy
between us.

34:23.322 --> 34:24.279
You know what I mean?

34:24.323 --> 34:26.151
Yeah,
I think I know why.

34:26.194 --> 34:27.326
Mm?

34:27.369 --> 34:29.110
I've been...

34:29.154 --> 34:30.590
working out
my crap lately,

34:30.633 --> 34:32.200
trying to figure out

34:32.244 --> 34:35.769
why I keep making
such messy decisions.

34:35.812 --> 34:39.294
So, what'd you figure out?

34:39.338 --> 34:43.516
That I've been recreating
my parents' marriage.

34:43.559 --> 34:45.735
That sounds twisted, but --

34:45.779 --> 34:46.954
Not really.

34:46.997 --> 34:49.522
That was me and Claire.

34:49.565 --> 34:51.654
My mom is cold.

34:51.698 --> 34:53.178
Then I married Claire,

34:53.221 --> 34:57.660
and she made my mom seem
warm and cuddly.

34:57.704 --> 35:01.621
But you helped me
break that pattern.

35:01.664 --> 35:04.493
I'm not exactly
warm and cuddly.

35:04.537 --> 35:05.842
[ Chuckles ]

35:05.886 --> 35:09.063
No,
you're something else.

35:09.107 --> 35:10.934
You're like
an open flame.

35:10.978 --> 35:12.197
[ Chuckles ]

35:15.722 --> 35:18.681
Andy,
you're not your mom, okay?

35:18.725 --> 35:20.901
No, I'm not.

35:20.944 --> 35:22.859
And you're not my dad.

35:22.903 --> 35:26.820
And...my mom leaving
was not my fault,

35:26.863 --> 35:30.737
and me leaving
is not my birthright.

35:33.348 --> 35:36.438
Do you think if we hadn't had
such messed-up parents,

35:36.482 --> 35:38.353
we could've made it?

35:38.397 --> 35:41.182
♪♪

35:41.226 --> 35:43.228
Maybe it was just
bad timing.

35:43.271 --> 35:44.968
♪♪

35:45.012 --> 35:46.927
Hey, my attorney said

35:46.970 --> 35:48.972
that the papers
haven't been filed yet.

35:49.016 --> 35:51.584
♪♪

35:51.627 --> 35:52.802
I'm taking them
out of the freezer.

35:52.846 --> 35:53.803
What?

35:53.847 --> 35:55.196
The papers.

35:55.240 --> 35:56.806
They've been in Maya
and Carina's freezer.

35:56.850 --> 35:58.808
[ Both laugh ]

35:58.852 --> 36:01.420
You put them
in the freezer?

36:01.463 --> 36:03.422
What's wrong with you?

36:03.465 --> 36:04.988
Like, next to the Popsicles?

36:05.032 --> 36:05.989
[ Laughs ]

36:06.033 --> 36:06.990
Ah...

36:07.034 --> 36:09.254
[ Laughs ]

36:09.297 --> 36:10.603
Ah...

36:10.646 --> 36:13.258
[ Laughs ]

36:13.301 --> 36:14.520
Yeah.

36:14.563 --> 36:23.224
♪♪

36:23.268 --> 36:27.402
[ Sighs ]

36:27.446 --> 36:29.012
Hey.

36:29.056 --> 36:30.405
[ Exhales sharply ]Hey.

36:30.449 --> 36:33.060
I figured
you were up here.

36:33.103 --> 36:35.367
Why are you not
in uniform?

36:35.410 --> 36:37.891
Uh, Gibson benched me.

36:37.934 --> 36:39.849
What?
Yeah.

36:39.893 --> 36:42.896
I don't know.
I deserved it.

36:42.939 --> 36:45.812
Vic.

36:47.509 --> 36:50.077
Listen, I know you've been
going through a lot lately,

36:50.120 --> 36:52.210
and, you know,
I'm trying to be here for you,

36:52.253 --> 36:53.341
but you know --

36:53.385 --> 36:55.213
I made out with Jack.

36:56.866 --> 36:58.390
W-- Uh,
"made out" is actually

36:58.433 --> 37:00.043
extremely generous
a description,

37:00.087 --> 37:01.828
which implies sexiness,
which there wasn't.

37:01.871 --> 37:05.135
There was zero sexiness,
but there was a lot of whiskey

37:05.179 --> 37:07.225
and we were smashing the tile
and we were sad.

37:07.268 --> 37:08.835
You smashed the tiles
like a week ago.

37:08.878 --> 37:10.750
Yeah,
I know, I know, I know,

37:10.793 --> 37:12.752
and I know
I should've told you sooner.

37:12.795 --> 37:14.232
I know that.

37:14.275 --> 37:16.059
Then --
Vic, stop.
Just stop.

37:18.453 --> 37:20.629
[ Sighs ]

37:20.673 --> 37:22.196
I'm sorry.
I pulled away from you

37:22.240 --> 37:25.721
instead of telling you
the truth, and I'm so...

37:25.765 --> 37:27.897
I don't have
an excuse.

37:31.727 --> 37:32.815
Do you hate me?

37:32.859 --> 37:35.514
No, I don't hate you, Vic.

37:35.557 --> 37:37.429
I wouldn't blame you
if you did.

37:40.258 --> 37:41.259
Were you
in love with him?

37:41.302 --> 37:44.262
What? Gibson?
No. Oh, my God, no.

37:44.305 --> 37:45.915
I told you, Theo,
it was not that.

37:45.959 --> 37:47.569
No, no, no.It wasn't even --

37:47.613 --> 37:49.005
No. Miller.

37:50.398 --> 37:52.226
Were you in love
with Miller?

